<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4831&amp;p=42942#p42942"><![CDATA[
"ACM" was just a marketing term (like Blast Processing) used to hype the game's extensive use of pre-rendered 3D graphics, something which was relatively new to console games. None of the three DKC games used any special mapper hardware or anything.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=935">BMF54123</a> — Thu Feb 05, 2009 10:46 pm</p><hr />
